<paragraph id="8BB33681FFCDFFE5A7868BBDFD429A08" blockId="12.[178,1085,388,534]" pageId="12" pageNumber="981">
N o t e: Feeding habits are unknown, probably feeds upon mooses and parasitic mushrooms (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B70FFCDFFE5A60C8BD0FE3299C5" author="PERICART J" box="[312,487,452,475]" pageId="12" pageNumber="981" pagination="84" refId="ref22080" refString="PERICART J. (1998 c): Hemipteres Lygaeidae euro-mediterraneens. In: Faune de France, t. 84 c. - Federation des Societes de sciences naturelles ed. Paris." type="book chapter" year="1998">PÉRICART 1998c</bibRefCitation>
), this author reports that the breeding of larvae has been tried successfully with seeds of Urticacea, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D02FFCDFFE5A5B68BF7FD3299E6" box="[642,743,482,504]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="12" pageNumber="981" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ericaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D02FFCDFFE5A5C28BF7FC7599E6" box="[758,928,482,504]" family="Chenopodiaceae" pageId="12" pageNumber="981" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
; euro Siberian until Central Asia and 
<collectingCountry id="F31B7611FFCDFFE5A6A38815FE049A0B" box="[407,465,512,533]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="981">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B70FFCDFFE5A6EB8815FD5E9A08" author="PERICART J" box="[479,651,510,534]" pageId="12" pageNumber="981" pagination="84" refId="ref22080" refString="PERICART J. (1998 c): Hemipteres Lygaeidae euro-mediterraneens. In: Faune de France, t. 84 c. - Federation des Societes de sciences naturelles ed. Paris." type="book chapter" year="1998">PÉRICART 1998c</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
